This paper is about control design for robots, specifically collaborative robots and space manipulators with significant joint flexibility. The use of a neural network for approximating unknown dynamics and online learning is a common technique in robotics, which suggests that this paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks for control design falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The control design also involves stability analysis, which is a common topic in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of online learning and backpropagation suggests that this paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
